 @Alan Beasy  Okay. Green house gas is a gas that traps and radiates infrared radiations of long wave length. Second if you didn't already know this, almost all gases composed of 3 or more atoms trap infrared heat and let me check the number of atoms in Co2. hmm...
1 atom of Carbon + 2 atoms of oxygen so 3 atoms. If you don't believe it then you are not only denying climate science you are denying chemistry. Thus: Co2 does cause warming. Thus an increase in Co2 causes an increase in warming.


Edit: By my last statement don't understand that an increase in Co2 almost definitely means an increase in warming. There are other factors.

 @DERMOT HENRY  I decided not to harass you anymore. I'm neither denier, nor advocate. I'm just passing through. Interesting topic though: One the one hand there the CC-advocates who say we're doomed (within five years to one hundred) and the CC-deniers, who say we're not and therefor we can continue screwing up things the way we do.
That shouldn't even be a point of discussion. Just wait and see and in the mean time, just go on doing what you're doing. There's nothing that can't be changed anyway according to the CC-advocates.
From an Irish person I would have expected to be more in favor of CC, having the Atlantic (the main heat carrier) on your doorstep, rather than being against it. Well, whatever, doesn't matter anyway. If you're here in five years, and I'm in Ireland by then, I'll buy you a descend drink, whatever they drink in Ireland.
